@NODE Introduction
AppXtrakt is a "little" tool to extract file(s) from Lha,Lzx & Zip archives.

I made this because i got Extractor V1.02 by RULER (Roland Szerletics) but i
can't use it with lzx archives for extracting only some files in 1 archive; 
I want too a tool where i can directly choose in a listview the file(s) i 
want to extract .

So i take CygnusEd, and start develloping AppXtrakt in AmigaE.

Features:
 - use @{"XADmaster.library" link xadmaster}
 - AppWindow
 - extract all files or only selected in LHA,LZX AND ZIP archives
 - extract all files in tgz archives (it's a beta version)
 - select path for destination (dir;volume;assign...)
 - show option with multiview
 - localized (English,deutsch,français)
 - some prefs in tooltypes 
 - Iconify & Appicon option
 - Arguments reading (Wb,Cli)
 - very intuitive !
 - display unpacked size of files
 - No limitation ;)
 - Written 100% in AmigaE.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Requirement

you only need ...

 - an Amiga V37+

 - Reqtools.library V38+ (does someone haven't this ? :))))
 - @{"XADmaster.library" link xadmaster} (Aminet:util/arc/xadmaster.lha)
 - Unzip (get Unzip V5.52 in Aminet:util/arc ???)
 - Untgz (get Untgz V1.5 in Aminet:util/arc ???)

 - Multiview
 - some libraries: utility37+, locale, icon33+, Workbench37+ ...

Developped on A1200/030/50/AGA/os3.1/32Mb  with AmigaE v3.3a

Tested on A500+ os2.0 and don't work ... sorry, try to get OS3.1 :)

@ENDNODE
@NODE Installation

 First, get @{"XADmaster.library" link xadmaster} and install it correctly!


 Just put it where you want ...
 
 I launch it with Toolmanager, as a Wb executable , with arguments "checked".

 Put Unzip & Untgz in c: or any "PATHed" dir ( Path >NIL: RAM: C: SYS:Rexxc ...)

 Put the appXtrakt.catalog in local/your country

 Modify the tooltypes for Source, Destination & Appicon path
  (default are Sys: ,Ram: & Progdir:appXtrakt)
  When started from cli, default options are used.
  Default is AppXtract.info in Progdir, without ".info" (see in tooltypes)


@{fg shine}Warning:@{fg text} if Appicon tooltype not found, appXtrakt won't start :(


 If you use DefIcon, put AppXtrakt as the default tool of Lha,Lzx & Zip deficons.


@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage
Well ... it's really hard :)

1. First, start it ! (if started from Lha/Lzx/Zip deficon, go to "3")

2. Then, drop an archive (Lha,Lzx or Zip) on it, or press the "file" button and 
   choose your archive via the requester.(Drop archive on appicon if iconified)
 
3. You can now see the content of the archive in the listview. 
   (the number is the unpacked size of the file, in bytes)

4. Select your destination with the "path" button ("RAM:" for Ram: ;)

5. Press "Xtract All" to extract all the files or ...

6. Select some files in the listview (u can see '*' before the file you selected)
   and press "Xtract Selected".


At last, when screen "flash", go to the destination you choose, and hoooo, 
the files are here!

The "show" button is to view some files with Multiview ...but only datatypes ;->
@ENDNODE
